==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Bridegroom
<hw>Bride"groom`</hw> <pr>(-gr⟦oomac⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>bridegome</ets>, <ets>brudgume</ets>, AS. <ets>br⟦ymac⟧dguma</ets>
(akin to OS. <ets>br⟦umac⟧digumo</ets>, D. <ets>bruidegom</ets>,
<ets>bruigom</ets>, OHG. <ets>pr⟦umac⟧tigomo</ets>, MHG.
<ets>briutegome</ets>, G. <ets>br⟦aum⟧utigam</ets>); AS.
<ets>br⟦ymac⟧d</ets> bride + <ets>guma</ets> man, akin to Goth.
<ets>guma</ets>, Icel. <ets>gumi</ets>, OHG. <ets>gomo</ets>, L.
<ets>homo</ets>; the insertion of <it>r</it> being caused by confusion
with <ets>groom</ets>. See <er>Bride</er>, and cf. <er>Groom</er>,
<er>Homage</er>.]</ety> <def>A man newly married, or just about to be
married.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

